{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01565T1Vp64AVTobTU7ADDR5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Multiarch Tuning Operator — Agent Navigation Hub\n2\t\n3\t## What This Operator Does\n4\t\n5\tThe Multiarch Tuning Operator enables architecture-aware pod scheduling on multi-architecture Kubernetes/OpenShift clusters. It intercepts newly created pods via a mutating webhook, adds a scheduling gate (`multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate`) to hold the pod before scheduling, inspects all container image manifests to determine which CPU architectures they support, writes a `nodeAffinity` requirement (and optionally a preferred scoring term) onto the pod, then removes the gate so the scheduler can place the pod on a compatible node.\n6\t\n7\tThe entire flow is driven by two pieces: a **mutating webhook** that gates pods, and a **pod reconciler** that inspects images, sets affinity, and ungatees pods.\n8\t\n9\t## Component Map\n10\t\n11\t| Component | Location | Mode flag | Purpose |\n12\t|---|---|---|---|\n13\t| Operator controller | `internal/controller/operator/` | `--enable-operator` | Manages CPPC CR lifecycle; deploys/tears down operands |\n14\t| Pod placement controller | `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_reconciler.go` | `--enable-ppc-controllers` | Watches gated pods, inspects images, sets nodeAffinity, removes gate |\n15\t| Mutating webhook | `internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook.go` | `--enable-ppc-webhook` | Adds scheduling gate to incoming pods |\n16\t| ENoExecEvent controllers | `internal/controller/enoexecevent/` | `--enable-enoexec-event-controllers` | Handles exec-format-error events from eBPF daemon |\n17\t| CPPC informer | `pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/` | `--enable-cppc-informer` | In-memory singleton of ClusterPodPlacementConfig for operand modes |\n18\t| Image inspector | `pkg/image/inspector.go` | (library) | Fetches image manifests, determines architectures, caches results |\n19\t| Pod model | `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go` | (library) | Core pod processing logic: gate management, affinity computation |\n20\t| Metrics | `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/` | (library) | Prometheus counters and histograms for controller and webhook |\n21\t| API types | `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` | (library) | ClusterPodPlacementConfig CRD; singleton, name must be \"cluster\" |\n22\t| Test builders | `pkg/testing/builder/` | (test-only) | Fluent builders for Kubernetes objects used in unit tests |\n23\t\n24\t## Key Workflows\n25\t\n26\t### Add a new field to ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec\n27\t\n28\t1. Edit `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` — add the field with kubebuilder validation tags.\n29\t2. Run `make manifests` first (generates CRD YAML and RBAC).\n30\t3. Run `make generate` (generates DeepCopy implementations).\n31\t4. Wire the field through the CPPC informer in `pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/` — do NOT call the Kubernetes API directly inside controllers; read from the informer singleton.\n32\t\n33\t### Add a new Prometheus metric\n34\t\n35\t1. Determine scope: controller metrics go in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go` (prefix `mto_ppo_ctrl_`); webhook metrics in `metrics/webhook.go` (prefix `mto_ppo_wh_`); shared metrics in `metrics/common_metrics.go`.\n36\t2. Declare a package-level `prometheus.Counter` / `prometheus.Histogram` variable.\n37\t3. Initialize and register it inside the corresponding `init*Metrics()` function using `metrics2.Registry.MustRegister(...)`.\n38\t4. Increment/observe the metric at the call site.\n39\t\n40\t### Write a unit test for the webhook\n41\t\n42\t1. Use Ginkgo `Describe`/`Context`/`It` blocks (never `t.Run`).\n43\t2. Construct test pods with the fluent builder: `builder.NewPod().WithName(\"test\").WithNamespace(\"default\").WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").Build()`.\n44\t3. Override `imageInspectionCache` (package-level `image.ICache` in `pod_model.go`) with a test double to avoid real registry calls.\n45\t4. Run focused tests with: `GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your test name'\" make unit`.\n46\t\n47\t### Add a new execution mode\n48\t\n49\t1. Add a `bool` flag variable and bind it in `bindFlags()` in `cmd/main.go`.\n50\t2. Add the mode to `validateFlags()` — exactly one mode must be set.\n51\t3. Construct a unique leader election ID by prefixing the base ID `208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io`.\n52\t4. Implement a `RunMyMode(mgr ctrl.Manager)` function and call it from `main()`.\n53\t5. If the mode needs ClusterPodPlacementConfig access, set `enableCPPCInformer = true` and start the syncer.\n54\t\n55\t## Troubleshooting\n56\t\n57\t| Symptom | Where to look |\n58\t|---|---|\n59\t| Pods stuck in `SchedulingGated` state | Check pod placement controller logs (`--enable-ppc-controllers`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` counter; verify pull secrets are accessible; check `MaxRetryCount` (5) not exhausted |\n60\t| Webhook not adding scheduling gate | Confirm `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` is present; check CPPC `namespaceSelector` — namespace may be excluded; verify pod is not in `kube-*` or operator namespace; check if pod is owned by DaemonSet |\n61\t| High image inspection latency | Cache may be cold after a global pull secret rotation (cache is cleared on `StoreGlobalPullSecret`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds` histogram; verify registry reachability |\n62\t| CPPC status shows Degraded | Check controller and webhook deployment rollout status; `PodPlacementControllerNotRolledOut` or `PodPlacementWebhookNotRolledOut` conditions will indicate which component is not ready |\n63\t| openshift-* pods getting gated unexpectedly | `openshift-*` namespaces are NOT hardcoded exclusions — configure `namespaceSelector` on ClusterPodPlacementConfig with `multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement DoesNotExist` |\n64\t\n65\t## Agentic Documentation\n66\t\n67\t| Document | Purpose |\n68\t|---|---|\n69\t| [agentic/DESIGN.md](agentic/DESIGN.md) | Architecture: pipeline, execution modes, singleton patterns, namespace exclusions |\n70\t| [agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md](agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md) | Step-by-step guides for adding fields, modes, and running code generation |\n71\t| [agentic/TESTING.md](agentic/TESTING.md) | Test pyramid, Ginkgo patterns, builder API, mocking image inspection |\n72\t| [agentic/RELIABILITY.md](agentic/RELIABILITY.md) | SLO targets, metric catalog, PromQL examples, alerting thresholds |\n73\t| [agentic/SECURITY.md](agentic/SECURITY.md) | Namespace exclusions as security controls, RBAC, webhook validation boundaries |\n74\t\n75\t### Component deep-dives\n76\t\n77\t- [Pod placement webhook](agentic/design-docs/components/pod-placement-webhook.md)\n78\t- [PPO controller](agentic/design-docs/components/ppo-controller.md)\n79\t- [Image inspection cache](agentic/design-docs/components/image-inspection-cache.md)\n80\t\n81\t### Concepts\n82\t\n83\t- [Execution modes](agentic/domain/concepts/execution-modes.md)\n84\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17f3279e-3ff4-4128-beca-9d4c7c1a551a","uuid":"5a76e7e8-6d80-422d-ba5f-5abd0b6f4985","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:20:58.729Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment/AGENTS.md","content":"# Multiarch Tuning Operator — Agent Navigation Hub\n\n## What This Operator Does\n\nThe Multiarch Tuning Operator enables architecture-aware pod scheduling on multi-architecture Kubernetes/OpenShift clusters. It intercepts newly created pods via a mutating webhook, adds a scheduling gate (`multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate`) to hold the pod before scheduling, inspects all container image manifests to determine which CPU architectures they support, writes a `nodeAffinity` requirement (and optionally a preferred scoring term) onto the pod, then removes the gate so the scheduler can place the pod on a compatible node.\n\nThe entire flow is driven by two pieces: a **mutating webhook** that gates pods, and a **pod reconciler** that inspects images, sets affinity, and ungatees pods.\n\n## Component Map\n\n| Component | Location | Mode flag | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Operator controller | `internal/controller/operator/` | `--enable-operator` | Manages CPPC CR lifecycle; deploys/tears down operands |\n| Pod placement controller | `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_reconciler.go` | `--enable-ppc-controllers` | Watches gated pods, inspects images, sets nodeAffinity, removes gate |\n| Mutating webhook | `internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook.go` | `--enable-ppc-webhook` | Adds scheduling gate to incoming pods |\n| ENoExecEvent controllers | `internal/controller/enoexecevent/` | `--enable-enoexec-event-controllers` | Handles exec-format-error events from eBPF daemon |\n| CPPC informer | `pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/` | `--enable-cppc-informer` | In-memory singleton of ClusterPodPlacementConfig for operand modes |\n| Image inspector | `pkg/image/inspector.go` | (library) | Fetches image manifests, determines architectures, caches results |\n| Pod model | `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go` | (library) | Core pod processing logic: gate management, affinity computation |\n| Metrics | `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/` | (library) | Prometheus counters and histograms for controller and webhook |\n| API types | `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` | (library) | ClusterPodPlacementConfig CRD; singleton, name must be \"cluster\" |\n| Test builders | `pkg/testing/builder/` | (test-only) | Fluent builders for Kubernetes objects used in unit tests |\n\n## Key Workflows\n\n### Add a new field to ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec\n\n1. Edit `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` — add the field with kubebuilder validation tags.\n2. Run `make manifests` first (generates CRD YAML and RBAC).\n3. Run `make generate` (generates DeepCopy implementations).\n4. Wire the field through the CPPC informer in `pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/` — do NOT call the Kubernetes API directly inside controllers; read from the informer singleton.\n\n### Add a new Prometheus metric\n\n1. Determine scope: controller metrics go in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go` (prefix `mto_ppo_ctrl_`); webhook metrics in `metrics/webhook.go` (prefix `mto_ppo_wh_`); shared metrics in `metrics/common_metrics.go`.\n2. Declare a package-level `prometheus.Counter` / `prometheus.Histogram` variable.\n3. Initialize and register it inside the corresponding `init*Metrics()` function using `metrics2.Registry.MustRegister(...)`.\n4. Increment/observe the metric at the call site.\n\n### Write a unit test for the webhook\n\n1. Use Ginkgo `Describe`/`Context`/`It` blocks (never `t.Run`).\n2. Construct test pods with the fluent builder: `builder.NewPod().WithName(\"test\").WithNamespace(\"default\").WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").Build()`.\n3. Override `imageInspectionCache` (package-level `image.ICache` in `pod_model.go`) with a test double to avoid real registry calls.\n4. Run focused tests with: `GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your test name'\" make unit`.\n\n### Add a new execution mode\n\n1. Add a `bool` flag variable and bind it in `bindFlags()` in `cmd/main.go`.\n2. Add the mode to `validateFlags()` — exactly one mode must be set.\n3. Construct a unique leader election ID by prefixing the base ID `208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io`.\n4. Implement a `RunMyMode(mgr ctrl.Manager)` function and call it from `main()`.\n5. If the mode needs ClusterPodPlacementConfig access, set `enableCPPCInformer = true` and start the syncer.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Where to look |\n|---|---|\n| Pods stuck in `SchedulingGated` state | Check pod placement controller logs (`--enable-ppc-controllers`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` counter; verify pull secrets are accessible; check `MaxRetryCount` (5) not exhausted |\n| Webhook not adding scheduling gate | Confirm `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` is present; check CPPC `namespaceSelector` — namespace may be excluded; verify pod is not in `kube-*` or operator namespace; check if pod is owned by DaemonSet |\n| High image inspection latency | Cache may be cold after a global pull secret rotation (cache is cleared on `StoreGlobalPullSecret`); check `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds` histogram; verify registry reachability |\n| CPPC status shows Degraded | Check controller and webhook deployment rollout status; `PodPlacementControllerNotRolledOut` or `PodPlacementWebhookNotRolledOut` conditions will indicate which component is not ready |\n| openshift-* pods getting gated unexpectedly | `openshift-*` namespaces are NOT hardcoded exclusions — configure `namespaceSelector` on ClusterPodPlacementConfig with `multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement DoesNotExist` |\n\n## Agentic Documentation\n\n| Document | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| [agentic/DESIGN.md](agentic/DESIGN.md) | Architecture: pipeline, execution modes, singleton patterns, namespace exclusions |\n| [agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md](agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md) | Step-by-step guides for adding fields, modes, and running code generation |\n| [agentic/TESTING.md](agentic/TESTING.md) | Test pyramid, Ginkgo patterns, builder API, mocking image inspection |\n| [agentic/RELIABILITY.md](agentic/RELIABILITY.md) | SLO targets, metric catalog, PromQL examples, alerting thresholds |\n| [agentic/SECURITY.md](agentic/SECURITY.md) | Namespace exclusions as security controls, RBAC, webhook validation boundaries |\n\n### Component deep-dives\n\n- [Pod placement webhook](agentic/design-docs/components/pod-placement-webhook.md)\n- [PPO controller](agentic/design-docs/components/ppo-controller.md)\n- [Image inspection cache](agentic/design-docs/components/image-inspection-cache.md)\n\n### Concepts\n\n- [Execution modes](agentic/domain/concepts/execution-modes.md)\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
