{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01KZtXmtwsG5ir5gTfi4ZtqS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Testing Guide: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n2\t\n3\t## Test Pyramid\n4\t\n5\tThe test suite is organized as approximately:\n6\t\n7\t- **70% unit tests** — co-located with source files as `*_test.go`, run with `make unit`. Use envtest for a fake API server. No cluster or registry required.\n8\t- **20% integration tests** — part of `make test`, exercise controller reconciliation loops against envtest with more realistic object graphs.\n9\t- **10% E2E tests** — in `pkg/e2e/`, require a live cluster with the operator deployed. Validate real image inspection from real registries.\n10\t\n11\t## Ginkgo BDD Structure\n12\t\n13\tAll tests use the Ginkgo/Gomega framework with BDD-style organization. Use `Describe`, `Context`, and `It` blocks. Never use `t.Run` — it is incompatible with Ginkgo's parallel runner and focused-test flags.\n14\t\n15\tCorrect structure:\n16\t\n17\t```go\n18\tvar _ = Describe(\"PodSchedulingGateMutatingWebHook\", func() {\n19\t    Context(\"when a pod is created in an included namespace\", func() {\n20\t        It(\"should add the scheduling gate\", func() {\n21\t            pod := builder.NewPod().\n22\t                WithName(\"test-pod\").\n23\t                WithNamespace(\"default\").\n24\t                WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").\n25\t                Build()\n26\t\n27\t            // ... exercise the webhook handler ...\n28\t\n29\t            Expect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).To(ContainElement(\n30\t                corev1.PodSchedulingGate{Name: utils.SchedulingGateName},\n31\t            ))\n32\t        })\n33\t    })\n34\t\n35\t    Context(\"when a pod is created in a kube-system namespace\", func() {\n36\t        It(\"should not add the scheduling gate\", func() {\n37\t            // ...\n38\t        })\n39\t    })\n40\t})\n41\t```\n42\t\n43\tNested `Context` blocks describe preconditions. `It` blocks describe a single assertion. Keep `It` blocks short and focused.\n44\t\n45\t## Fluent Builder API\n46\t\n47\tTest code in this repository must construct Kubernetes objects using the fluent builders in `pkg/testing/builder/`. Never instantiate raw structs like `&corev1.Pod{}` directly — raw structs omit required fields, produce brittle tests, and are harder to read.\n48\t\n49\t### Pod builder\n50\t\n51\t```go\n52\timport \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n53\t\n54\t// Minimal pod with one container\n55\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n56\t    WithName(\"my-pod\").\n57\t    WithNamespace(\"default\").\n58\t    WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").\n59\t    Build()\n60\t\n61\t// Pod with scheduling gate, multiple containers, and init containers\n62\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n63\t    WithName(\"gated-pod\").\n64\t    WithNamespace(\"default\").\n65\t    WithSchedulingGates(\"multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate\").\n66\t    WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\", \"quay.io/example/sidecar:v1\").\n67\t    WithInitContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/init:v1\").\n68\t    WithLabels(\"app\", \"myapp\", \"version\", \"v1\").\n69\t    Build()\n70\t\n71\t// Pod with existing nodeAffinity\n72\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n73\t    WithName(\"affinity-pod\").\n74\t    WithNodeSelectorTermsMatchExpressions(\n75\t        []corev1.NodeSelectorRequirement{\n76\t            {Key: \"kubernetes.io/arch\", Operator: corev1.NodeSelectorOpIn, Values: []string{\"amd64\"}},\n77\t        },\n78\t    ).\n79\t    Build()\n80\t\n81\t// Pod owned by a DaemonSet (webhook should ignore it)\n82\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n83\t    WithName(\"ds-pod\").\n84\t    WithOwnerReference(metav1.OwnerReference{\n85\t        Kind: \"DaemonSet\",\n86\t        Name: \"my-ds\",\n87\t    }).\n88\t    Build()\n89\t```\n90\t\n91\tBuilder methods available for pods: `WithName`, `WithNamespace`, `WithGenerateName`, `WithContainersImages`, `WithContainer`, `WithContainerImagePullAlways`, `WithInitContainersImages`, `WithImagePullSecrets`, `WithSchedulingGates`, `WithNodeName`, `WithNodeSelectors`, `WithAffinity`, `WithNodeAffinity`, `WithNodeSelectorTermsMatchExpressions`, `WithPreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution`, `WithOwnerReference`, `WithOwnerReferences`, `WithLabels`, `WithAnnotations`, `WithContainerStatuses`.\n92\t\n93\tOther available builders (see `pkg/testing/builder/`): `NewDeployment`, `NewNode`, `NewSecret`, `NewConfigMap`, `NewClusterPodPlacementConfig`, `NewMutatingWebhookConfiguration`, and many more.\n94\t\n95\t## Mocking Image Inspection\n96\t\n97\tReal image inspection requires network access to a container registry and CGO dependencies. Unit tests must avoid this by overriding the `imageInspectionCache` package-level variable in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go`:\n98\t\n99\t```go\n100\tvar imageInspectionCache image.ICache = image.FacadeSingleton()\n101\t```\n102\t\n103\tBecause this is a package-level variable (not a constructor argument), tests override it directly:\n104\t\n105\t```go\n106\timport (\n107\t    \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/internal/controller/podplacement\"\n108\t    \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/image\"\n109\t    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/sets\"\n110\t)\n111\t\n112\t// In BeforeEach or at the top of a Describe block:\n113\tvar fakeCache *fakeImageCache\n114\t\n115\tBeforeEach(func() {\n116\t    fakeCache = &fakeImageCache{\n117\t        architectures: sets.New(\"amd64\", \"arm64\"),\n118\t    }\n119\t    // Override the package-level variable\n120\t    podplacement.SetImageInspectionCache(fakeCache)\n121\t})\n122\t\n123\tAfterEach(func() {\n124\t    // Restore the real cache to avoid leaking state between tests\n125\t    podplacement.SetImageInspectionCache(image.FacadeSingleton())\n126\t})\n127\t```\n128\t\n129\tImplement `fakeImageCache` with the `image.ICache` interface:\n130\t\n131\t```go\n132\ttype fakeImageCache struct {\n133\t    architectures sets.Set[string]\n134\t    err           error\n135\t}\n136\t\n137\tfunc (f *fakeImageCache) GetCompatibleArchitecturesSet(\n138\t    ctx context.Context, imageReference string, skipCache bool, secrets [][]byte,\n139\t) (sets.Set[string], error) {\n140\t    return f.architectures, f.err\n141\t}\n142\t```\n143\t\n144\tFor tests that simulate inspection failure, set `err` to a non-nil error to trigger the retry/fallback logic.\n145\t\n146\t## Running Focused Tests\n147\t\n148\t```bash\n149\t# Run all unit tests\n150\tmake unit\n151\t\n152\t# Focus on a specific test by description substring\n153\tGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='should add scheduling gate'\" make unit\n154\t\n155\t# Focus on a Describe block\n156\tGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='PodSchedulingGateMutatingWebHook'\" make unit\n157\t\n158\t# Run without Docker (faster iteration)\n159\tNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your pattern'\" make unit\n160\t\n161\t# Run with verbose output and show all skipped tests\n162\tGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your pattern' --always-emit-ginkgo-writer\" make unit\n163\t```\n164\t\n165\tThe `--focus` flag uses Ginkgo's built-in filtering, which matches against the full concatenated description string (`Describe text + Context text + It text`). A partial substring match is sufficient.\n166\t\n167\tCoverage reports are written to `test-unit-coverage.out` in the repository root.\n168\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17f3279e-3ff4-4128-beca-9d4c7c1a551a","uuid":"b723e136-101b-4735-996f-79e8c1756792","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:21:07.456Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment/agentic/TESTING.md","content":"# Testing Guide: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n\n## Test Pyramid\n\nThe test suite is organized as approximately:\n\n- **70% unit tests** — co-located with source files as `*_test.go`, run with `make unit`. Use envtest for a fake API server. No cluster or registry required.\n- **20% integration tests** — part of `make test`, exercise controller reconciliation loops against envtest with more realistic object graphs.\n- **10% E2E tests** — in `pkg/e2e/`, require a live cluster with the operator deployed. Validate real image inspection from real registries.\n\n## Ginkgo BDD Structure\n\nAll tests use the Ginkgo/Gomega framework with BDD-style organization. Use `Describe`, `Context`, and `It` blocks. Never use `t.Run` — it is incompatible with Ginkgo's parallel runner and focused-test flags.\n\nCorrect structure:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"PodSchedulingGateMutatingWebHook\", func() {\n    Context(\"when a pod is created in an included namespace\", func() {\n        It(\"should add the scheduling gate\", func() {\n            pod := builder.NewPod().\n                WithName(\"test-pod\").\n                WithNamespace(\"default\").\n                WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").\n                Build()\n\n            // ... exercise the webhook handler ...\n\n            Expect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).To(ContainElement(\n                corev1.PodSchedulingGate{Name: utils.SchedulingGateName},\n            ))\n        })\n    })\n\n    Context(\"when a pod is created in a kube-system namespace\", func() {\n        It(\"should not add the scheduling gate\", func() {\n            // ...\n        })\n    })\n})\n```\n\nNested `Context` blocks describe preconditions. `It` blocks describe a single assertion. Keep `It` blocks short and focused.\n\n## Fluent Builder API\n\nTest code in this repository must construct Kubernetes objects using the fluent builders in `pkg/testing/builder/`. Never instantiate raw structs like `&corev1.Pod{}` directly — raw structs omit required fields, produce brittle tests, and are harder to read.\n\n### Pod builder\n\n```go\nimport \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\n// Minimal pod with one container\npod := builder.NewPod().\n    WithName(\"my-pod\").\n    WithNamespace(\"default\").\n    WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\").\n    Build()\n\n// Pod with scheduling gate, multiple containers, and init containers\npod := builder.NewPod().\n    WithName(\"gated-pod\").\n    WithNamespace(\"default\").\n    WithSchedulingGates(\"multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate\").\n    WithContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/app:latest\", \"quay.io/example/sidecar:v1\").\n    WithInitContainersImages(\"quay.io/example/init:v1\").\n    WithLabels(\"app\", \"myapp\", \"version\", \"v1\").\n    Build()\n\n// Pod with existing nodeAffinity\npod := builder.NewPod().\n    WithName(\"affinity-pod\").\n    WithNodeSelectorTermsMatchExpressions(\n        []corev1.NodeSelectorRequirement{\n            {Key: \"kubernetes.io/arch\", Operator: corev1.NodeSelectorOpIn, Values: []string{\"amd64\"}},\n        },\n    ).\n    Build()\n\n// Pod owned by a DaemonSet (webhook should ignore it)\npod := builder.NewPod().\n    WithName(\"ds-pod\").\n    WithOwnerReference(metav1.OwnerReference{\n        Kind: \"DaemonSet\",\n        Name: \"my-ds\",\n    }).\n    Build()\n```\n\nBuilder methods available for pods: `WithName`, `WithNamespace`, `WithGenerateName`, `WithContainersImages`, `WithContainer`, `WithContainerImagePullAlways`, `WithInitContainersImages`, `WithImagePullSecrets`, `WithSchedulingGates`, `WithNodeName`, `WithNodeSelectors`, `WithAffinity`, `WithNodeAffinity`, `WithNodeSelectorTermsMatchExpressions`, `WithPreferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution`, `WithOwnerReference`, `WithOwnerReferences`, `WithLabels`, `WithAnnotations`, `WithContainerStatuses`.\n\nOther available builders (see `pkg/testing/builder/`): `NewDeployment`, `NewNode`, `NewSecret`, `NewConfigMap`, `NewClusterPodPlacementConfig`, `NewMutatingWebhookConfiguration`, and many more.\n\n## Mocking Image Inspection\n\nReal image inspection requires network access to a container registry and CGO dependencies. Unit tests must avoid this by overriding the `imageInspectionCache` package-level variable in `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go`:\n\n```go\nvar imageInspectionCache image.ICache = image.FacadeSingleton()\n```\n\nBecause this is a package-level variable (not a constructor argument), tests override it directly:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/internal/controller/podplacement\"\n    \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/image\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/sets\"\n)\n\n// In BeforeEach or at the top of a Describe block:\nvar fakeCache *fakeImageCache\n\nBeforeEach(func() {\n    fakeCache = &fakeImageCache{\n        architectures: sets.New(\"amd64\", \"arm64\"),\n    }\n    // Override the package-level variable\n    podplacement.SetImageInspectionCache(fakeCache)\n})\n\nAfterEach(func() {\n    // Restore the real cache to avoid leaking state between tests\n    podplacement.SetImageInspectionCache(image.FacadeSingleton())\n})\n```\n\nImplement `fakeImageCache` with the `image.ICache` interface:\n\n```go\ntype fakeImageCache struct {\n    architectures sets.Set[string]\n    err           error\n}\n\nfunc (f *fakeImageCache) GetCompatibleArchitecturesSet(\n    ctx context.Context, imageReference string, skipCache bool, secrets [][]byte,\n) (sets.Set[string], error) {\n    return f.architectures, f.err\n}\n```\n\nFor tests that simulate inspection failure, set `err` to a non-nil error to trigger the retry/fallback logic.\n\n## Running Focused Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all unit tests\nmake unit\n\n# Focus on a specific test by description substring\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='should add scheduling gate'\" make unit\n\n# Focus on a Describe block\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='PodSchedulingGateMutatingWebHook'\" make unit\n\n# Run without Docker (faster iteration)\nNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your pattern'\" make unit\n\n# Run with verbose output and show all skipped tests\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='your pattern' --always-emit-ginkgo-writer\" make unit\n```\n\nThe `--focus` flag uses Ginkgo's built-in filtering, which matches against the full concatenated description string (`Describe text + Context text + It text`). A partial substring match is sufficient.\n\nCoverage reports are written to `test-unit-coverage.out` in the repository root.\n","numLines":168,"startLine":1,"totalLines":168}}}
