{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01B54YNpjr5Fv1xDmLXuHxNV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, there's a `WithNamespaceSelector` method. Now I have everything I need to write the implementation.\n\nHere's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## File to modify\n\n**`internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go`**\n\n### Changes\n\nAdd imports for `corev1`, `metav1`, and `utils`. Add a new `Context` block inside the existing `When` block that creates a pod in `openshift-kube-apiserver` with a control plane node selector and verifies the scheduling gate is NOT added.\n\nHere is the complete modified file:\n\n```go\npackage podplacement\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\timgspecv1 \"github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/specs-go/v1\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/image/fake/registry\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Internal/Controller/PodPlacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook\", func() {\n\tWhen(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", func() {\n\t\tContext(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should ignore pods with a non-empty nodeName\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"test-namespace\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeName(\"test-node-name\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t\tContext(\"is handling a pod in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not add the scheduling gate to a pod with a control plane node selector\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tns := &corev1.Namespace{\n\t\t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tName: \"openshift-kube-apiserver\",\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, ns)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create namespace\")\n\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr = k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(\n\t\t\t\t\tcorev1.PodSchedulingGate{Name: utils.SchedulingGateName},\n\t\t\t\t))\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n### What changed\n\n1. **Added imports**: `corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"`, `metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"`, and `\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"`.\n\n2. **Added a new `Context` block** (sibling to the existing \"is handling the mutation of pods\" context) that:\n   - Creates the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace in the envtest API server\n   - Builds a pod using the fluent builder API with:\n     - A container image from the test registry\n     - `WithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\")` (matching the existing pattern)\n     - `WithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\")`\n     - `WithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\")` — this is the key: kube-apiserver pods in OpenShift have the `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` node selector, which causes `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` to return `true` in `shouldIgnorePod`\n   - Creates the pod via `k8sClient.Create`, which triggers the mutating webhook\n   - Asserts that `pod.Spec.SchedulingGates` does NOT contain the `multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate` entry\n\n### Why this works\n\nThe namespace `openshift-kube-apiserver` starts with `openshift-`, NOT `kube-`, so the `strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"kube-\")` check in `shouldIgnorePod` does NOT exclude it. Instead, the pod is excluded because `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` returns `true` (the pod has `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` in its `nodeSelector`). The test verifies this exclusion works even though the CPPC's namespaceSelector effectively matches all namespaces (in the test environment, the `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` has no `NamespaceSelector`, so the webhook fires for every namespace).\n\n### Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# Run just this test\nNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='openshift-kube-apiserver'\" make unit\n\n# Or run the full webhook test suite\nNO_DOCKER=1 GINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook'\" make unit\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":248,"cache_read_input_tokens":81686,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":248,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17f3279e-3ff4-4128-beca-9d4c7c1a551a","uuid":"a3a310e3-0a6d-4738-8234-cb939630790d","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:27:26.464Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDhg8qkxAn8WkYyrFFZj"}
